examples.en: She sucked on an orange slice.
The fluid was sucked from his lungs.
The baby sucked on the mother's breast.
They sucked in deep lungfuls of air.
She just sucked her teeth and stared.
Baby waved a sucked pink thumb at him.
He got the promotion only because he sucked up to his manager.
The tide almost sucked us out to sea.
They waited in silence and sucked their sweets.
A bird was sucked into one of the jet's engines.
The boat was sucked under the water in the storm.
Jennie sucked up the last bit of milkshake with her straw.
As the sun got hotter, it sucked up the mist from the sea.
Michael put the cigarette to his lips and sucked in the smoke.
The current boom in the economy sucked many workers in from abroad.
She was sucked in by a scam that was run by a shady outfit selling time-shares.
